I'm leaving.

00:26:40.799 --> 00:26:47.806 line:95%,end
Yes, I'm leaving Berlin.

00:26:48.440 --> 00:26:49.741 line:95%,end
Whoa, yes.

00:26:49.808 --> 00:26:53.211 line:95%,end
I'm leaving.

00:26:53.278 --> 00:26:57.215 line:95%,end
Yes, I'm leaving.

00:26:57.282 --> 00:27:04.289 line:95%,end
Yes, I'm leaving Berlin.

00:27:13.765 --> 00:27:16.067 line:95%,end
[cheering]

00:27:20.071 --> 00:27:21.840 line:95%,end
That was beautiful, Maddie.
Thank you.

00:27:22.574 --> 00:27:24.676 line:95%,end
All right, I'm joined
by all the moms here on stage.

00:27:24.743 --> 00:27:28.113 line:95%,end
So, ladies, it's been a wild, wild season.

00:27:28.179 --> 00:27:30.315 line:95%,end
- JILL: Yeah.
- [laughs]

00:27:30.382 --> 00:27:31.850 line:95%,end
Kelly, when we were out here
before with you and Christi

00:27:31.916 --> 00:27:33.618 line:95%,end
and we were having
the conversation about did she,

00:27:33.685 --> 00:27:36.121 line:95%,end
did she not call you,
you said that you wanted

00:27:36.187 --> 00:27:37.288 line:95%,end
to set the record straight.

00:27:37.355 --> 00:27:39.924 line:95%,end
I went to her house
right after I took the girls to school,

00:27:40.025 --> 00:27:40.959 line:95%,end
and it was 8:30 in the morning.

00:27:41.026 --> 00:27:43.361 line:95%,end
She called her from her house,
and I watched her.

00:27:43.428 --> 00:27:45.196 line:95%,end
- Yeah.
- That's a lie, and you know it.

00:27:45.263 --> 00:27:47.232 line:95%,end
There was something going on that week,

00:27:47.298 --> 00:27:49.100 line:95%,end
and you were pissed off,
and you didn't call me.

00:27:49.167 --> 00:27:51.703 line:95%,end
So you can sit here and try
to be the bigger person on television--

00:27:51.770 --> 00:27:54.272 line:95%,end
Let me just say that
the phone goes both ways, sister.

00:27:54.339 --> 00:27:55.874 line:95%,end
Yes, but I was having a bad time.

00:27:55.940 --> 00:27:58.109 line:95%,end
And whenever you're having problems,
I call you.

00:27:58.176 --> 00:28:00.412 line:95%,end
- Yeah, and I call you, too.
- I was having problems with all of this--

00:28:00.478 --> 00:28:01.880 line:95%,end
- And you can ask every one--
- --and you didn't call.

00:28:01.946 --> 00:28:03.081 line:95%,end
--of these women, that entire week,

00:28:03.148 --> 00:28:04.416 line:95%,end
- did I not stick up for her--
- CHRISTI: I know.

00:28:04.616 --> 00:28:06.551 line:95%,end
- KELLY: --every single time? Great.
- You're great, and I'm wrong.

00:28:06.618 --> 00:28:08.787 line:95%,end
But you know what?
You were being a bitch, too.

00:28:08.853 --> 00:28:11.523 line:95%,end
- [gasping]
- OK, but I called you.

00:28:11.589 --> 00:28:14.726 line:95%,end
So by the time there was a phone call,
you were both pissed?

00:28:14.793 --> 00:28:15.794 line:95%,end
- Yeah.
- All right.

00:28:15.860 --> 00:28:17.962 line:95%,end
Well, let's find out
what the audience has to ask.

00:28:18.029 --> 00:28:19.497 line:95%,end
Who's got a question for the ladies?

00:28:19.564 --> 00:28:21.499 line:95%,end
My question is for Melissa.

00:28:21.566 --> 00:28:24.135 line:95%,end
Can you tell us
how Broadway Baby's death affected you

00:28:24.202 --> 00:28:25.804 line:95%,end
and why it was so important to you

00:28:25.870 --> 00:28:28.306 line:95%,end
to dedicate Maddie's solo to him?

00:28:28.373 --> 00:28:32.110 line:95%,end
Well, I babysat Baby several times.

00:28:32.177 --> 00:28:34.813 line:95%,end
And I was close to her dog.

00:28:34.879 --> 00:28:37.449 line:95%,end
I think I'm a big dog lover,
and you can ask any of them.

00:28:37.515 --> 00:28:39.918 line:95%,end
Yeah. But remember,
we weren't allowed to dedicate--

00:28:39.984 --> 00:28:40.819 line:95%,end
- Yeah.
- --the group number.

00:28:40.885 --> 00:28:42.554 line:95%,end
- I think it was--
- JILL: We weren't allowed to touch that.

00:28:42.620 --> 00:28:44.155 line:95%,end
We all have regrets,
and that was something

00:28:44.222 --> 00:28:45.390 line:95%,end
that I do regret doing.

00:28:45.457 --> 00:28:50.028 line:95%,end
And I think it was pretty stupid
on my part that I did that.

00:28:51.029 --> 00:28:52.363 line:95%,end
- Well, that's fair.
- MELISSA: I do-- I do.

00:28:52.430 --> 00:28:54.566 line:95%,end
I'm going to give her that, yeah.
Who else has an audience question?

00:28:54.632 --> 00:28:57.669 line:95%,end
Kelly and Christi,
were you hurt that you weren't invited

00:28:57.736 --> 00:28:59.003 line:95%,end
to Melissa's wedding?

00:28:59.838 --> 00:29:04.175 line:95%,end
No. I'm not surprised that I wasn't
invited to Melissa's wedding. Were you?

00:29:04.242 --> 00:29:08.346 line:95%,end
I thought it was strange
that we're together 24 hours a day.

00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:09.781 line:95%,end
- I mean--
- For sure.

00:29:09.848 --> 00:29:13.017 line:95%,end
--I just thought it was weird
that we weren't included in the wedding.

00:29:13.084 --> 00:29:16.721 line:95%,end
But guess what? I'm very happily married,
and I didn't have a big wedding.

00:29:16.788 --> 00:29:18.656 line:95%,end
- I know, but that's what--
- MELISSA: It's not--

00:29:18.723 --> 00:29:20.191 line:95%,end
I didn't do anything
behind anybody's back.

00:29:20.258 --> 00:29:21.359 line:95%,end
JILL: --a wedding is.

00:29:21.426 --> 00:29:23.561 line:95%,end
I'm having a party,
and everyone's invited to that.

00:29:23.628 --> 00:29:26.131 line:95%,end
All right. Let's take another question
from the audience.

00:29:26.197 --> 00:29:27.132 line:95%,end
Who has a question for one of the ladies?

00:29:28.633 --> 00:29:32.070 line:95%,end
Hi. Mackenzie never danced
because she was injured.

00:29:32.537 --> 00:29:34.572 line:95%,end
And then she went on
to dance on "The View."

00:29:34.639 --> 00:29:36.608 line:95%,end
How do you all feel about that?

00:29:36.674 --> 00:29:38.209 line:95%,end
Well, I'll speak up, because I--

00:29:38.276 --> 00:29:41.212 line:95%,end
I was-- I spoke up
for Melissa at "The View."

00:29:41.279 --> 00:29:43.515 line:95%,end
Mackenzie's been a part of this team.

00:29:43.581 --> 00:29:46.851 line:95%,end
She-- She was on the award-winning team

00:29:46.918 --> 00:29:48.486 line:95%,end
that won Nationals.

00:29:48.553 --> 00:29:51.322 line:95%,end
It was only right for her
to dance at "The View."

00:29:51.389 --> 00:29:53.158 line:95%,end
I don't think
it was ever a question of Macken--

00:29:53.224 --> 00:29:55.393 line:95%,end
if it was right for Mackenzie
to dance on "The View."


00:29:55.460 --> 00:29:59.497 line:95%,end
I think the problem was Melissa
herself made a huge deal

00:29:59.564 --> 00:30:00.832 line:95%,end
about Mackenzie's foot injury.

00:30:00.899 --> 00:30:02.066 line:95%,end
Mackenzie may never dance again.

00:30:02.133 --> 00:30:03.835 line:95%,end
- She's gonna have to live with this--
- I never said that.

00:30:03.902 --> 00:30:05.436 line:95%,end
I mean, does everyone remember
her saying that?

00:30:05.503 --> 00:30:06.704 line:95%,end
- I--
- Thank you.

00:30:06.771 --> 00:30:08.039 line:95%,end
- She said--
- It came across that way.

00:30:08.106 --> 00:30:10.341 line:95%,end
- CHRISTI: She may never be able--
- OK, but I never said, "Oh, my God,

00:30:10.408 --> 00:30:11.509 line:95%,end
she's never gonna dance again.

00:30:11.643 --> 00:30:13.745 line:95%,end
You're the one
who made the big deal of it.

00:30:13.812 --> 00:30:15.246 line:95%,end
You took her to all these doctors.

00:30:15.313 --> 00:30:18.683 line:95%,end
She showed up in an Aircast
when she was to dance against Asia.

00:30:18.750 --> 00:30:20.385 line:95%,end
That was before Asia.
I'm sorry.

00:30:20.451 --> 00:30:22.854 line:95%,end
Her foot was hurting
weeks before Asia came.

00:30:23.154 --> 00:30:26.124 line:95%,end
I think what everyone's problem was

00:30:26.191 --> 00:30:28.793 line:95%,end
is that you made such a big deal
out of the foot.

00:30:28.860 --> 00:30:31.930 line:95%,end
And then all of a sudden,
it was miraculously healed.

00:30:31.996 --> 00:30:33.531 line:95%,end
- It was like whoopee, healed.
- MELISSA: She didn't--

00:30:33.598 --> 00:30:34.732 line:95%,end
- It's "The View."
- MELISSA: --dance on her foot.

00:30:34.799 --> 00:30:36.100 line:95%,end
- Her foot is better.
- Oh, my God.

00:30:36.167 --> 00:30:37.268 line:95%,end
You make [bleep] up all the time.

00:30:37.502 --> 00:30:39.103 line:95%,end
[crowd murmuring]

00:30:39.204 --> 00:30:41.372 line:95%,end
I've got a question.
Who wants to talk about Cathy?

00:30:41.639 --> 00:30:42.841 line:95%,end
Not me.

00:30:42.907 --> 00:30:44.242 line:95%,end
- [groaning]
- Nah.

00:30:44.309 --> 00:30:46.611 line:95%,end
So Jill, you had the biggest fight
of the season

00:30:46.678 --> 00:30:50.248 line:95%,end
- with Cathy this year.
- I think Cathy was very disrespectful.

00:30:50.315 --> 00:30:51.916 line:95%,end
I don't regret what I did.

00:30:51.983 --> 00:30:54.819 line:95%,end
I think I had every right
to be angry at her,

00:30:54.886 --> 00:30:56.221 line:95%,end
and I'm still angry at her.

00:30:56.287 --> 00:30:57.989 line:95%,end
She never apologized.

00:30:58.056 --> 00:30:59.991 line:95%,end
She runs her mouth
and says things she shouldn't say--

00:31:00.058 --> 00:31:00.892 line:95%,end
Oh, oh.

00:31:00.959 --> 00:31:02.760 line:5%,start
- I run my mouth and you don't?
- --about children.

00:31:02.827 --> 00:31:03.895 line:5%,start
Say it to my face.

00:31:03.962 --> 00:31:04.829 line:5%,start
- Say it to me.
- You know-- [scoffs]

00:31:04.896 --> 00:31:06.698 line:95%,end
- She's saying it behind my back.
- Well, Jill, she's here.

00:31:06.764 --> 00:31:09.801 line:95%,end
She's the leader of the Candy Apples
and the Apple Cores.

00:31:09.868 --> 00:31:11.035 line:95%,end
Please welcome Cathy.

00:31:11.102 --> 00:31:14.005 line:95%,end
[upbeat music]

00:31:14.072 --> 00:31:16.374 line:95%,end
[cheering]

00:31:20.278 --> 00:31:23.248 line:95%,end
I got a question for you. It seems
like when we were watching this season,

00:31:23.314 --> 00:31:26.451 line:95%,end
that your relationship
with Jill and with Abby

00:31:26.517 --> 00:31:27.352 line:95%,end
has really escalated.

00:31:27.418 --> 00:31:28.753 line:95%,end
It's taken a nosedive.

00:31:28.820 --> 00:31:32.690 line:95%,end
I think that Abby
is just about to implode.

00:31:32.757 --> 00:31:34.492 line:95%,end
She's totally ignoring me now.

00:31:34.559 --> 00:31:36.494 line:95%,end
She won't even say my name, exc--

00:31:36.561 --> 00:31:38.763 line:95%,end
- Oh, you're like Chloe.
- Yeah, you're right.

00:31:38.830 --> 00:31:40.498 line:95%,end
She doesn't know
how to say Chloe's name either.

00:31:40.565 --> 00:31:43.468 line:95%,end
The only time that she does
say my name, I understand,

00:31:43.534 --> 00:31:45.169 line:95%,end
is when she's holding her meet and greets

00:31:45.236 --> 00:31:47.605 line:95%,end
and she wants to tell people
that I don't have a dance studio,

00:31:47.672 --> 00:31:50.408 line:95%,end
that I'm a terrible dance teacher
and this, that, and the other.

00:31:50.475 --> 00:31:53.177 line:95%,end
But really, in the grand scheme
of those-- those comments,

00:31:53.244 --> 00:31:56.180 line:95%,end
she's giving me publicity.
So I do need to thank her.

00:31:56.247 --> 00:31:59.484 line:95%,end
So as long as she keeps talking about me,
I know that she's threatened by me.

00:31:59.550 --> 00:32:01.019 line:95%,end
But that's why she doesn't say your name.

00:32:01.085 --> 00:32:02.353 line:95%,end
I don't think she's threatened by you.

00:32:02.420 --> 00:32:04.689 line:95%,end
She's threatened
by the team that I've put together.

00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:07.191 line:95%,end
And I'm not doing
anything differently than she is.

00:32:07.258 --> 00:32:08.359 line:95%,end
Jill, I got a question for you.

00:32:08.426 --> 00:32:09.460 line:95%,end
Before Cathy came out here,

00:32:09.527 --> 00:32:11.129 line:95%,end
you said you were still
very upset with her.

00:32:11.195 --> 00:32:14.899 line:95%,end
I think it's disrespectful
to talk about a child.

00:32:14.966 --> 00:32:18.469 line:95%,end
OK. I have every right
as a dance teacher to critique.

00:32:18.536 --> 00:32:21.839 line:95%,end
If I were talking about Kendall,
saying, "Oh, that kid is so ugly

00:32:21.906 --> 00:32:23.574 line:95%,end
and I can't stand that kid,
she's a brat",

00:32:23.641 --> 00:32:25.343 line:95%,end
but what was said

00:32:25.410 --> 00:32:27.145 line:95%,end
- was all constructive critiquing.
- JILL: No.

00:32:27.211 --> 00:32:28.646 line:95%,end
- It really wasn't.
- CATHY: What was it that I said?

00:32:28.713 --> 00:32:32.750 line:95%,end
It was disrespectful and rude
saying she has to hide behind a mask.

00:32:32.817 --> 00:32:34.886 line:95%,end
And you know you said it to be--

00:32:34.953 --> 00:32:36.354 line:95%,end
CATHY: But--
- --to get me going.

00:32:36.421 --> 00:32:37.555 line:95%,end
But you know-- JILL: And you did, so--

00:32:37.622 --> 00:32:38.756 line:95%,end
- But you know what, Jill?
- --you win.

00:32:38.823 --> 00:32:40.858 line:95%,end
Ultimately, I have the right to say that.

00:32:40.925 --> 00:32:43.561 line:95%,end
OK. So what-- what's your excuse
for doing it to Paige?

00:32:43.628 --> 00:32:45.063 line:95%,end
I did not do that to Paige.

00:32:45.129 --> 00:32:46.831 line:95%,end
Abby set your kid up.

00:32:46.898 --> 00:32:48.499 line:95%,end
And you need to know that, Kelly.

00:32:48.566 --> 00:32:49.801 line:95%,end
And I 100% agree.

00:32:49.867 --> 00:32:51.402 line:95%,end
You were clear down on the other end.

00:32:51.469 --> 00:32:52.837 line:95%,end
- You didn't even hear--
- Yeah, but I heard.

00:32:52.904 --> 00:32:54.739 line:95%,end
- CATHY: --that Anthony--
- We heard everything that was said.

00:32:54.906 --> 00:32:56.574 line:95%,end
She didn't hear.
She wasn't even near.

00:32:56.808 --> 00:33:00.044 line:95%,end
Let's do this. Let's find out
who has a question for-- for Cathy.

00:33:00.111 --> 00:33:01.713 line:95%,end
Cathy, what do you think about Jill?

00:33:01.779 --> 00:33:03.815 line:95%,end
For one, I think she's a studio-hopper.

00:33:03.915 --> 00:33:06.451 line:95%,end
And I had several students
who were on my team

00:33:06.517 --> 00:33:07.552 line:95%,end
last year that left,

00:33:07.652 --> 00:33:11.089 line:95%,end
and Jill has tried to befriend them
and sidle up to them for information.

00:33:11.155 --> 00:33:13.424 line:95%,end
Let me jump in right here, ladies.
I wanna thank you so much.

00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:16.728 line:95%,end
So, ladies, next up,
with an acrobatic, lyrical solo

00:33:16.794 --> 00:33:19.430 line:95%,end
