JILL: Get out!

00:35:04.869 --> 00:35:06.037 line:95%,end
CATHY: Oh, my god. You are such--

00:35:06.104 --> 00:35:07.205 line:95%,end
JILL: You're gonna
hit me with your purse?

00:35:07.271 --> 00:35:08.473 line:95%,end
--a [bleep] bitch.

00:35:08.539 --> 00:35:10.575 line:95%,end
That woman just hit me.

00:35:10.641 --> 00:35:12.543 line:95%,end
Go ahead.
Water doesn't hurt me.

00:35:12.610 --> 00:35:13.544 line:95%,end
Grow up!

00:35:13.611 --> 00:35:14.745 line:95%,end
CATHY: You grow up!

00:35:14.812 --> 00:35:15.713 line:95%,end
[cheering]

00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:16.848 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:35:17.081 --> 00:35:19.083 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Living on the dance floor.

00:35:19.150 --> 00:35:20.952 line:95%,end
As you can see, Abby's returned.

00:35:21.018 --> 00:35:22.053 line:95%,end
So look, I want to get right to it.

00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:24.822 line:95%,end
Last season, the biggest,
most explosive moment

00:35:24.889 --> 00:35:27.158 line:95%,end
the fans saw
was an altercation between you and Cathy

00:35:27.225 --> 00:35:29.093 line:95%,end
that got physical, let's say.

00:35:29.160 --> 00:35:30.828 line:95%,end
Cathy, when you look back at that footage

00:35:30.895 --> 00:35:33.331 line:95%,end
and you see yourself
hitting Abby with a purse,

00:35:33.431 --> 00:35:34.899 line:95%,end
what do you think?

00:35:34.966 --> 00:35:38.169 line:95%,end
First of all, I don't consider that a hit.
It was a swat.

00:35:38.269 --> 00:35:39.837 line:95%,end
And the purse was this big.

00:35:39.904 --> 00:35:41.839 line:95%,end
It was a little patent leather purse.

00:35:41.906 --> 00:35:45.143 line:95%,end
And I'm sure that Abby's flu shot
hurt a heck of a lot worse

00:35:45.209 --> 00:35:46.577 line:95%,end
than the little swat.

00:35:46.644 --> 00:35:47.912 line:95%,end
And what do you think?

00:35:47.979 --> 00:35:52.350 line:95%,end
Oh, before she comments, I wanna add
that the reason that happened

00:35:52.416 --> 00:35:54.585 line:95%,end
- was because she threw water on me.
- Is that true?

00:35:54.652 --> 00:35:55.686 line:95%,end
You did throw water on her.

00:35:55.753 --> 00:35:57.788 line:95%,end
No, I did not throw water on her.

00:35:57.855 --> 00:35:59.090 line:95%,end
If I would have thrown water on her,

00:35:59.157 --> 00:36:00.424 line:95%,end
I would have hit her right in the face.

00:36:00.491 --> 00:36:02.026 line:95%,end
OK, so the sprinkler system
was going off.

00:36:02.093 --> 00:36:03.928 line:95%,end
- And no, I took--
- CATHY: Was that it was?

00:36:03.995 --> 00:36:07.598 line:95%,end
I took a bottle of water
that I had been drinking earlier.

00:36:07.999 --> 00:36:11.335 line:95%,end
And I said, "Let's see if she melts--"

00:36:11.402 --> 00:36:14.472 line:95%,end
- No, that's not how it went.
- --as in the Wicked Witch.

00:36:14.539 --> 00:36:17.008 line:95%,end
And the force of the water
inside the bottle

00:36:17.275 --> 00:36:19.076 line:95%,end
shoved the cap off the bottle.

00:36:19.277 --> 00:36:22.880 line:95%,end
You clearly hear me apologize
immediately and say, I'm sorry.

00:36:22.947 --> 00:36:24.949 line:95%,end
- Oh, no.
-I did not mean that to happen

00:36:25.016 --> 00:36:26.150 line:95%,end
You-- you did not apologize.

00:36:26.217 --> 00:36:30.254 line:95%,end
And then this psychotic
goes off and smacks me

00:36:30.321 --> 00:36:31.589 line:95%,end
- in the back with a pocketbook.
- Swat.

00:36:31.656 --> 00:36:32.924 line:95%,end
I swatted you. And it probably--

00:36:32.990 --> 00:36:33.925 line:95%,end
- Doesn't matter.
- --didn't even hurt.

00:36:33.991 --> 00:36:35.493 line:95%,end
When you strike another person--

00:36:35.560 --> 00:36:36.594 line:95%,end
- It probably didn't even hurt.
- --you have crossed the line.

00:36:36.661 --> 00:36:37.995 line:95%,end
- Well, then you shouldn't--
- End.

00:36:38.062 --> 00:36:39.463 line:95%,end
--throw water at people,
whether you want to play around

00:36:39.530 --> 00:36:41.832 line:95%,end
and say that you wanna see if the Wicked
Witch is going to melt or not.

00:36:41.899 --> 00:36:45.069 line:95%,end
So if you would have never done that,
none of this would have happened.

00:36:45.136 --> 00:36:48.206 line:95%,end
And I would not have to talk
to the back of your head all the time.

00:36:48.406 --> 00:36:50.007 line:95%,end
Melissa took pictures of my bruises.

00:36:50.074 --> 00:36:52.076 line:95%,end
Oh, you hardly had bruises.

00:36:52.176 --> 00:36:56.147 line:95%,end
You act as though
this 90-pound weakling beat you up.

00:36:56.214 --> 00:36:57.982 line:95%,end
Cathy, then you came swinging at me.

00:36:58.049 --> 00:36:59.150 line:95%,end
After you poured-- listen--

00:36:59.217 --> 00:37:00.484 line:95%,end
- It doesn't matter.
- CATHY: Oh, it does--

00:37:00.551 --> 00:37:02.420 line:95%,end
- You don't hit.
- CATHY: --matter. You poured water on me!

00:37:02.486 --> 00:37:03.588 line:95%,end
You beat up Abby!

00:37:03.654 --> 00:37:05.456 line:95%,end
When did you become her bodyguard?

00:37:05.523 --> 00:37:07.658 line:95%,end
You should have just sat down and let Abby

00:37:07.725 --> 00:37:09.794 line:95%,end
and I finalize what was going on.

00:37:09.860 --> 00:37:11.696 line:95%,end
You did not need to get involved.

00:37:11.829 --> 00:37:14.966 line:95%,end
Well, I think we can all agree
that hitting and throwing water,

00:37:15.032 --> 00:37:16.334 line:95%,end
those things probably
shouldn't happen in the future.

00:37:16.467 --> 00:37:17.401 line:95%,end
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:37:17.468 --> 00:37:18.836 line:95%,end
All right.
Let's see what the audience has to say.

00:37:18.903 --> 00:37:20.938 line:95%,end
Hi.
My question's for Abby.

00:37:21.005 --> 00:37:24.675 line:95%,end
So, Abby, in Detroit,
you told Cathy to go to hell.

00:37:24.775 --> 00:37:27.778 line:95%,end
I was just wondering
if you've ever said anything

00:37:27.845 --> 00:37:30.314 line:95%,end
- that you regret in front of the kids.
- No.

00:37:30.381 --> 00:37:32.416 line:95%,end
- Oh.
- On any normal given day,

00:37:32.483 --> 00:37:34.685 line:95%,end
I don't normally swear.

00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:36.220 line:95%,end
But because I showed up in a limo

00:37:36.287 --> 00:37:39.457 line:95%,end
and she was upset and jealous
and rattled, she had to swear.

00:37:39.523 --> 00:37:41.959 line:95%,end
I have-- a driver picked me up
in every single airport

00:37:42.026 --> 00:37:44.362 line:95%,end
for every promotion I do for "Dance Moms."

00:37:44.428 --> 00:37:45.529 line:95%,end
That's not a big deal.

00:37:45.596 --> 00:37:47.265 line:95%,end
Then start taking your team that way,

00:37:47.531 --> 00:37:50.635 line:95%,end
instead of-- instead of making them
go by themselves.

00:37:50.701 --> 00:37:52.536 line:95%,end
I don't need to take my team that way.

00:37:52.670 --> 00:37:55.172 line:95%,end
Why? Why can't you do something nice
for them once in a while?


00:37:55.239 --> 00:37:56.274 line:95%,end
Yeah. But you came out,

00:37:56.340 --> 00:37:58.209 line:95%,end
and you wanted to rub it
in all of our faces.

00:37:58.276 --> 00:38:00.511 line:95%,end
- CATHY: Well, does she not--
- I do not solicit students.

00:38:00.611 --> 00:38:03.547 line:95%,end
Does she not-- neither do I.
Do you know something I don't know?

00:38:03.614 --> 00:38:05.049 line:95%,end
How do I solicit those students?

00:38:05.116 --> 00:38:07.685 line:95%,end
I know that every single one of those boys
would rather be dancing for me.

00:38:07.752 --> 00:38:09.220 line:95%,end
Oh, I don't think so, Abby.

00:38:09.287 --> 00:38:10.821 line:95%,end
Let's take another question
from the audience.

00:38:10.888 --> 00:38:12.189 line:95%,end
Who's got a question
for one of the ladies?

00:38:12.857 --> 00:38:16.160 line:95%,end
Have any of you ever heard
Abby say I'm sorry?

00:38:16.494 --> 00:38:18.696 line:95%,end
- Oh, no.
- No.

00:38:18.763 --> 00:38:20.665 line:95%,end
- She apologized to Cathy--
- Oh, she apologized to-- yeah.

00:38:20.731 --> 00:38:21.999 line:95%,end
- She said to that Cathy.
- --from throwing water on her.

00:38:22.066 --> 00:38:23.868 line:95%,end
- But--
- MELISSA: Yes.

00:38:23.934 --> 00:38:24.935 line:95%,end
--I don't-- I don't know
about to the children.

00:38:25.002 --> 00:38:26.170 line:95%,end
Well, listen. Thank you, ladies.

00:38:26.237 --> 00:38:27.371 line:95%,end
It's time for the last
number of the night.

00:38:27.438 --> 00:38:29.340 line:95%,end
Now this performance
was really controversial.

00:38:29.407 --> 00:38:31.542 line:95%,end
I did this piece 12 years ago.

00:38:31.609 --> 00:38:36.714 line:95%,end
And it was in the headlines then,
and it's still happening.

